10/07/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The ruling Social Democratic Party (PSD) is preparing for the 2004-2005 elections. The PSD Council decided Wednesday (9 July) that a new political strategy, aimed at securing a majority in parliament in the next elections, should be drafted by 25 September. Prime Minister Adrian Nastase says the party's main political priorities would include enhancing economic growth, combating corruption, and reforming the political system in line with the EU integration process. (Rompres - 09/07/03)
